articles.headline: Spencer Shrader converts from 45 yards after penalty on 60-yard miss and Colts beat Broncos 29-28
articles.description: Indianapolis Colts kicker Spencer Shrader missed one opportunity to beat the Denver Broncos.

images.name: Colts stun Broncos after penalty gives Indy a second chance
images.caption: Spencer Shrader misses his initial kick, but the Broncos are called for a personal foul, giving the Colts a second chance which is converted for a game-winning field goal.

articles.headline: Sources: Bengals' Joe Burrow may need surgery for turf toe
articles.description: Star Cincinnati Bengals quarterback Joe Burrow is dealing with a turf toe injury that could need surgery, sources told ESPN's Adam Schefter on Sunday night.

images.name: Joe Burrow heads to the locker room with apparent leg injury
images.caption: Joe Burrow goes to the locker room after suffering an apparent leg injury in the second quarter.

articles.headline: Falcons-Vikings NFL Week 2 highlights
articles.description: The Falcons and Vikings face off in a Week 2 matchup Sunday night, and we have all the major highlights.

articles.headline: Lions make point against Ben Johnson, Bears with 52-21 rout
articles.description: In a game they called "personal," the Lions scored 52 points on former offensive coordinator Ben Johnson, whose Bears dropped to 0-2 in his first season.

images.name: Ben Johnson/Dan Campbell  [600x600]
images.caption: Ben Johnson and Dan Campbell embrace after Sunday's game, the first between the two since Johnson left his offensive coordinator job in Detroit to be Chicago's coach.

images.name: Amon-Ra St. Brown hauls in his 3rd TD of the game
images.caption: Jared Goff and Amon-Ra St. Brown connect for a 3rd time to pad the Lions lead.

articles.headline: Calais Campbell's sack with 26 seconds left secures Cardinals' 27-22 win after Carolina comeback try
articles.description: Calais Campbell and his 39-year-old body came up with a game-ending sack to help the Arizona Cardinals secure a 27-22 win on Sunday over the Carolina Panthers, turning back a frantic...

images.name: Young, Renfrow link up for another TD connection
images.caption: Bryce Young gets the Panthers closer to the Cardinals with another touchdown pass to Hunter Renfrow.

articles.headline: Bears' defense throttled again in Detroit
articles.description: Just like the last time the Bears visited Detroit, they came away searching for answers after getting routed.

images.name: Chicago Bears defense [1296x729]
images.caption: The Bears had not given up 52 points in 11 years, even during the rough days with Matt Eberflus as coach. Eberflus, by the way, visits Soldier Field as the Cowboys defensive coordinator Sunday.

images.caption: Jared Goff and Amon-Ra St. Brown connect for a 3rd time to pad the Lions lead.
